// - Otto executes untrusted JavaScript; there is no built-in sandbox strong enough for hostile code.
// - We mitigate common abuse by (1) reusing a VM, (2) setting an interrupt-based timeout per item,
//   and (3) disallowing access to Go values by injecting a JSON-like copy (map/slice primitives only).
// - If you need stronger isolation, run scripts in a separate process/container.

